      "id": "theory_hex_to_dec",
      "title": "Converting Hex to Decimal",
      "content": "Converting hexadecimal to decimal is similar to converting binary to decimal, but we use powers of 16 instead of powers of 2!\n\n**Step-by-Step Method:**\n\n1. Write down the hex number\n2. Write the position values (powers of 16) below each digit\n3. Convert any letter digits to decimal (A=10, B=11, ... F=15)\n4. Multiply each digit by its position value\n5. Add all the results\n\n**Example 1: Convert 2A to decimal**\n\nHex:       2    A\nPositions: 16   1\nValues:    2    10 (A=10)\nCalculate: 2\u00d716 10\u00d71\nResults:   32 + 10 = 42\n\nSo 2A in hex = 42 in decimal!\n\n**Example 2: Convert 1F3 to decimal**\n\nHex:       1    F    3\nPositions: 256  16   1\nValues:    1    15   3\nCalculate: 1\u00d7256 15\u00d716 3\u00d71\nResults:   256 + 240 + 3 = 499\n\nSo 1F3 in hex = 499 in decimal!\n\n**Common Hex Values to Remember:**\n\u2022 F = 15\n\u2022 FF = 255 (very common in colors!)\n\u2022 100 = 256\n\u2022 FFF = 4095\n\nRemember: Always convert letter digits (A-F) to their decimal values (10-15) before calculating!"
    },
